{
  "video_id": "JwhouCNq-Fc",
  "title": "What makes a poem … a poem? - Melissa Kovacs",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 7039.0,
      "end_time": 11069.0,
      "text": "Muhammad Ali spent years training to become the greatest boxer"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 11069.0,
      "end_time": 13520.0,
      "text": "the world had ever seen,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 13520.0,
      "end_time": 17149.0,
      "text": "but only moments to create the shortest poem."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 17149.0,
      "end_time": 21250.0,
      "text": "Ali captivated Harvard's  graduating class in 1975"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 21250.0,
      "end_time": 24680.0,
      "text": "with his message of unity and friendship."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 24680.0,
      "end_time": 27371.0,
      "text": "When he finished,  the audience wanted more."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 27371.0,
      "end_time": 29060.0,
      "text": "They wanted a poem."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 29060.0,
      "end_time": 32962.0,
      "text": "Ali delivered what is considered the shortest poem ever."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 32962.0,
      "end_time": 35661.0,
      "text": "\"Me, we.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 35661.0,
      "end_time": 38271.0,
      "text": "Or is it \"me, weeee\"?"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 38271.0,
      "end_time": 39481.0,
      "text": "No one's really sure."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 39481.0,
      "end_time": 45471.0,
      "text": "Regardless, if these two words are a poem, then what exactly makes a poem a poem?"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 45471.0,
      "end_time": 48101.0,
      "text": "Poets themselves have struggled with this question,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 48101.0,
      "end_time": 51605.0,
      "text": "often using metaphors to approximate a definition."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 51605.0,
      "end_time": 53680.0,
      "text": "Is a poem a little machine?"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 53680.0,
      "end_time": 54765.0,
      "text": "A firework?"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 54765.0,
      "end_time": 55821.0,
      "text": "An echo?"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 55821.0,
      "end_time": 57010.0,
      "text": "A dream?"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 57010.0,
      "end_time": 61352.0,
      "text": "Poetry generally has certain recognizable characteristics."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 61352.0,
      "end_time": 65551.0,
      "text": "One - poems emphasize language's musical qualities."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 65551.0,
      "end_time": 68481.0,
      "text": "This can be achieved through rhyme, rhythm, and meter,"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 68481.0,
      "end_time": 69979.0,
      "text": "from the sonnets of Shakepeare,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 69979.0,
      "end_time": 71542.0,
      "text": "to the odes of Confucius,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 71542.0,
      "end_time": 73852.0,
      "text": "to the Sanskrit Vedas."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 73852.0,
      "end_time": 76556.0,
      "text": "Two - poems use condensed language,"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 76556.0,
      "end_time": 80492.0,
      "text": "like literature with all the water wrung out of it."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 80492.0,
      "end_time": 83872.0,
      "text": "Three - poems often feature intense feelings,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 83872.0,
      "end_time": 85875.0,
      "text": "from Rumi's spiritual poetry"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 85875.0,
      "end_time": 89312.0,
      "text": "to Pablo Neruda's \"Ode to an Onion.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 89312.0,
      "end_time": 93883.0,
      "text": "Poetry, like art itself, has a way of challenging simple definitions."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 93883.0,
      "end_time": 96303.0,
      "text": "While the rhythmic patterns  of the earliest poems"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 96303.0,
      "end_time": 100163.0,
      "text": "were a way to remember stories even before the advent of writing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 100163.0,
      "end_time": 102703.0,
      "text": "a poem doesn't need to be lyrical."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 102703.0,
      "end_time": 104251.0,
      "text": "Reinhard Döhl's “Apfel”"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 104251.0,
      "end_time": 106649.0,
      "text": "and Eugen Gomringer's \"silencio\""
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 106649.0,
      "end_time": 110160.0,
      "text": "toe the line between visual art and poetry."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 110160.0,
      "end_time": 113556.0,
      "text": "Meanwhile, E.E. Cummings wrote poems whose shapes were as important"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 113556.0,
      "end_time": 115420.0,
      "text": "as the words themselves,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 115420.0,
      "end_time": 121909.0,
      "text": "in this case amplifying the sad loneliness of a single leaf falling through space."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 121909.0,
      "end_time": 125569.0,
      "text": "If the visual nature of poetry faded into the background,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 125569.0,
      "end_time": 127989.0,
      "text": "perhaps we'd be left with music,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 127989.0,
      "end_time": 130600.0,
      "text": "and that's an area that people love to debate."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 130600.0,
      "end_time": 132669.0,
      "text": "Are songs poems?"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 132669.0,
      "end_time": 136189.0,
      "text": "Many don't regard songwriters as poets in a literary sense,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 136189.0,
      "end_time": 138689.0,
      "text": "but lyrics from artists like Paul Simon,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 138689.0,
      "end_time": 139788.0,
      "text": "Bob Dylan"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 139788.0,
      "end_time": 141159.0,
      "text": "和 Tupac Shakur"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 141159.0,
      "end_time": 143829.0,
      "text": "often hold up even without the music."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 143829.0,
      "end_time": 147049.0,
      "text": "In rap, poet elements like rhyme, rhythm, and imagery"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 147049.0,
      "end_time": 149529.0,
      "text": "are inseparable from the form."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 149529.0,
      "end_time": 152359.0,
      "text": "Take this lyric from the Notorious B.I.G."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 152359.0,
      "end_time": 154727.0,
      "text": "\"I can hear sweat trickling  down your cheek"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 154727.0,
      "end_time": 157019.0,
      "text": "Your heartbeat sound  like Sasquatch feet"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 157019.0,
      "end_time": 159801.0,
      "text": "Thundering, shaking the concrete.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 159801.0,
      "end_time": 163298.0,
      "text": "So far, all the examples we've seen have had line breaks."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 163298.0,
      "end_time": 168045.0,
      "text": "We can even imagine the two words of Ali's poem organizing in the air -"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 168045.0,
      "end_time": 170258.0,
      "text": "Me, We."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 170258.0,
      "end_time": 173304.0,
      "text": "Poetry has a shape  that we can usually recognize."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 173304.0,
      "end_time": 177209.0,
      "text": "Its line breaks help readers navigate the rhythms of a poem."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 177209.0,
      "end_time": 179628.0,
      "text": "But what if those line breaks disappeared?"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 179628.0,
      "end_time": 182118.0,
      "text": "Would it lose its essence as a poem?"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 182118.0,
      "end_time": 183433.0,
      "text": "Maybe not."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 183433.0,
      "end_time": 185237.0,
      "text": "Enter the prose poem."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 185237.0,
      "end_time": 187989.0,
      "text": "Prose poems use vivid images and wordplay"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 187989.0,
      "end_time": 191271.0,
      "text": "but are formatted like paragraphs."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 191271.0,
      "end_time": 195343.0,
      "text": "When we look at poetry less as a form and more as a concept,"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 195343.0,
      "end_time": 198149.0,
      "text": "we can see the poetic all around us:"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 198149.0,
      "end_time": 199378.0,
      "text": "spiritual hymns,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 199378.0,
      "end_time": 202249.0,
      "text": "the speeches of orators like Martin Luther King, Jr.,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 202249.0,
      "end_time": 203179.0,
      "text": "JFK,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 203179.0,
      "end_time": 204590.0,
      "text": "and Winston Churchill,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 204590.0,
      "end_time": 207429.0,
      "text": "and surprising places like social media."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 207429.0,
      "end_time": 213140.0,
      "text": "In 2010, journalist Joanna Smith tweeted updates from the earthquake in Haiti."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 213140.0,
      "end_time": 216091.0,
      "text": "\"Was in b-room getting dressed when heard my name."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 216091.0,
      "end_time": 218811.0,
      "text": "Tremor. Ran outside through sliding door."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 218811.0,
      "end_time": 222531.0,
      "text": "All still now. Safe. Roosters crowing.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 222531.0,
      "end_time": 226061.0,
      "text": "Smith uses language in a way that is powerful, direct,"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 226061.0,
      "end_time": 228273.0,
      "text": "and filled with vivid images."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 228273.0,
      "end_time": 230723.0,
      "text": "Compare her language to a haiku,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 230723.0,
      "end_time": 235823.0,
      "text": "the ancient Japanese poetic form  that emphasizes bursts of brief intensity"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 235823.0,
      "end_time": 240684.0,
      "text": "with just three lines of five,  seven, and five syllables."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 240684.0,
      "end_time": 243632.0,
      "text": "The waters of poetry run wide and deep."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 243632.0,
      "end_time": 245504.0,
      "text": "Poetry has evolved over time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 245504.0,
      "end_time": 247193.0,
      "text": "and perhaps now more than ever,"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 247193.0,
      "end_time": 252854.0,
      "text": "the line between poetry,  prose, song, and visual art has blurred."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 252854.0,
      "end_time": 255234.0,
      "text": "However, one thing has not changed."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 255234.0,
      "end_time": 258664.0,
      "text": "The word poetry actually began in verb form,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 258664.0,
      "end_time": 263604.0,
      "text": "coming from the ancient Greek poiesis, which means to create."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 263604.0,
      "end_time": 268144.0,
      "text": "Poets, like craftsman, still work with the raw materials of the world"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 268144.0,
      "end_time": 269992.0,
      "text": "to forge new understandings"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 269992.0,
      "end_time": 276075.0,
      "text": "and comment on what it is to be human in a way only humans can."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 276075.0,
      "end_time": 281525.0,
      "text": "Dartmouth researchers tested this idea by asking robots to pen poetry."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 281525.0,
      "end_time": 285024.0,
      "text": "A panel of judges sorted  through stacks of sonnets"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 285024.0,
      "end_time": 289054.0,
      "text": "to see if they could distinguish those made by man and machine."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 289054.0,
      "end_time": 293012.0,
      "text": "You may be happy to know that while scientists have successfully"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 293012.0,
      "end_time": 296035.0,
      "text": "used artificial intelligence  in manufacturing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 296035.0,
      "end_time": 297035.0,
      "text": "medicine,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 297035.0,
      "end_time": 298575.0,
      "text": "and even journalism,"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 298575.0,
      "end_time": 301255.0,
      "text": "poetry is a different story."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 301255.0,
      "end_time": 311255.0,
      "text": "The robots were caught red-handed 100% of the time."
    }
  ]
}